      • allowNullOrigin

        public CorsOptions allowNullOrigin()
        Web browsers may set the 'Origin' request header to 'null' if a resource is loaded from the local file system. Calling this method will enable a successful CORS response with a "null" value for the CORS response header 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin'.
        返回:
        CorsOptions to support method chaining.

      • exposeHeaders

        public CorsOptions exposeHeaders(String... headers)
        Specifies the headers to be exposed to calling clients.

        During a simple CORS request, only certain response headers are made available by the browser, for example using: 

         xhr.getResponseHeader("Content-Type");

        The headers that are available by default are:

        • Cache-Control
        • Content-Language
        • Content-Type
        • Expires
        • Last-Modified
        • Pragma

        To expose other headers they need to be specified which is what this method enables by adding the headers to the CORS 'Access-Control-Expose-Headers' response header.

        参数:
        headers - the values to be added to the 'Access-Control-Expose-Headers' response header
        返回:
        CorsOptions to support method chaining.

      • allowCredentials

        public CorsOptions allowCredentials()
        By default cookies are not included in CORS requests, but this method will enable cookies to be added to CORS requests. Calling this method will set the CORS 'Access-Control-Allow-Credentials' response header to true.

        Please note, that cookie support needs to be enabled on the client side as well. The client needs to opt-in to send cookies by calling: 

         xhr.withCredentials = true;
        The default value for 'withCredentials' is false in which case no cookies are sent. Setting this to true will included cookies in cross origin requests.
        返回:
        CorsOptions to support method chaining.

      • maxAge

        public CorsOptions maxAge(long max)
        When making a preflight request the client has to perform two request with can be inefficient. This setting will set the CORS 'Access-Control-Max-Age' response header and enables the caching of the preflight response for the specified time. During this time no preflight request will be made.
        参数:
        max - the maximum time, in seconds, that the preflight response may be cached.
        返回:
        CorsOptions to support method chaining.

      • allowedMethods

        public CorsOptions allowedMethods(HttpMethod... methods)
        Specifies the allowed set of HTTP Request Methods that should be returned in the CORS 'Access-Control-Request-Method' response header.
        参数:
        methods - the HttpMethods that should be allowed.
        返回:
        CorsOptions to support method chaining.

      • allowedHeaders

        public CorsOptions allowedHeaders(String... headers)
        Specifies the if headers that should be returned in the CORS 'Access-Control-Allow-Headers' response header.

        If a client specifies headers on the request, for example by calling: 

         xhr.setRequestHeader('My-Custom-Header', "SomeValue");
        the server will receive the above header name in the 'Access-Control-Request-Headers' of the preflight request. The server will then decide if it allows this header to be sent for the real request (remember that a preflight is not the real request but a request asking the server if it allow a request).
        参数:
        headers - the headers to be added to the preflight 'Access-Control-Allow-Headers' response header.
        返回:
        CorsConfigBuilder to support method chaining.
